omaticity","last_activity_date":1446776386,"creation_date":1367819767,"answer_count":3,"title":"Histidine aromaticity","body":"<p>I understand that the imidazole ring in histidine is aromatic. I also realize that it retains it's aromaticity when protonated.\nI am wondering why it is not mentioned at all in basic text books such as Lehninger? Also, across the web there are a number of places claiming that histidine isn't aromatic in all cases. \nAnother reason I am a little confused is, if protonation doesn't harm the aromatic nature, then why is histidine such a weak base?\nAm I missing something?<\/p>\n","question_id":8206,"tags":["biochemistry","amino-acids"],"score":6,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":2895,"up_vote_count":6},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96340076c030ada6a204f9030a9853b8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19826,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19826/steve-robbins","reputation":111,"display_name":"Steve Robbins"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/0la1I.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4833,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4833/dexter","reputation":1808,"display_name":"Dexter"},"score":0,"post_id":40267,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446639245,"comment_id":67669,"body":"I think it is subjective phenomenon."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"score":0,"post_id":40267,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446774971,"comment_id":67803,"body":"I don&#39;t know about you, but I can walk around in only a T-shirt when the air temperature is 10&#176;C, but jumping into 10&#176;C water is going to be a world of pain... This should really be a chemistry or physics question about specific heat capacity."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"