lenish the lost fresh water. This also requires that they pump out the excess salt in the sea water they drink using their kidneys and specialized chloride cells in their gills.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/EfkvT.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/EfkvT.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Some more information can be found <a href=\"http://www.amnh.org/exhibitions/past-exhibitions/water-h2o-life/life-in-water/surviving-in-salt-water\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a>, or you can watch a short video on the subject <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pvc4DTwpm_g\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n","answer_id":40252,"question_id":40239,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1446579689}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/40239/do-saltwater-fish-need-to-drink","last_activity_date":1446579689,"creation_date":1446551328,"answer_count":1,"title":"Do saltwater fish need to drink?","body":"<p>In my biology class we got the question if saltwater fish need to drink. We need to use the term osmosis, but I cannot think of a valid answer and we were allowed to ask help.<\/p>\n","question_id":40239,"tags":["ichthyology","osmosis"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":40252,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"duplicate","is_answered":true,"view_count":60,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1446551359},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/793a5b28c923ea4bda67af914e80ec72?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3078,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3078/anuj-mehta","reputation":14,"display_name":"Anuj Mehta"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/78GJV.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19650,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19650/yvide","reputation":1952,"display_name":"YviDe"},"score":6,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1446577473,"creation_date":1446544171,"body":"<p>With humans infected with malaria, 