othing more than <em>D. foetida<\/em>?<\/li>\n<li>Since these formerly-recognised infraspecific taxa do exist as separately-kept lines in cultivation, would they be properly recognised as cultivars?<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>My answer may simply be the closing remark in the above-quoted description, \"Since the various forms are connected by intermediates, it is impossible to recognize infraspecific taxa.\" However, that's deeply-unsatisfying if cataloguing a collection that contains several now-synonymous specimens.<\/p>\n","question_id":39970,"tags":["botany","taxonomy"],"score":4,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":55,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1445904166},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/fMQ8h.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":13396,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13396/franklin-p-combs","reputation":126,"display_name":"Franklin P Combs"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef69e4c7ba6adf44fc3d17c4bbacec01?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":10401,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10401/tanmath","reputation":1620,"display_name":"TanMath","accept_rate":58},"score":0,"post_id":40171,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446411467,"comment_id":67447,"body":"They certainly do look like calcium oxalate crystals!"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"score":0,"post_id":40171,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446421374,"comment_id":67457,"body":"You just reproduced some of Louis Pasteur&#39;s work. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Pasteur#Molecular_asymmetry\" rel=\"nofollow\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Pasteur#Molecular_asymmetry<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16